# 4. 決まらない贈り物

Mafuyu: Okay, we're here.
Minori: Wow, they have so much cute stuff! And...at reasonable prices too!
Airi: This is my first time actually visiting, but I'd heard they have a nice selection of goods.
Mafuyu: Yes, they apparently carry quite a few rare items.
Minori: A cute trinket might work just as well as snacks when it comes to White Day...!
Mafuyu: Hehe. Valentine's Day is usually all about chocolates, but many people seem to give each other cosmetics and little gifts like these for White Day.
Ichika: Yes, it is nice that we have those as options...
Kanade: I agree. We might just be able to find what we're looking for here...
Airi: Then, let's start looking!
Kanade: Okay.
Mafuyu: Excuse me. I'd like to have all of these wrapped as gifts.
Clerk: Yes, of course. I'll get started on these right away. In the meantime, please feel free to continue browsing.
Mafuyu: Understood. Thank you very much.
Kanade: Is this a sketchbook...? It's tiny, but Ena might really like it.
Kanade: And this looks like a fancy teaspoon... Ms. Mochizuki would... Wait, she probably already has one like this.
Ichika: This is still really hard...
Mafuyu: I don't think that you should think so hard about this.
Mafuyu: Those two would probably love to receive this sketchbook and teaspoon from you.
Kanade: Oh... Yes, I agree...
Kanade: I know they'd like these... But it doesn't seem like enough to just get them gifts that they'll enjoy. It just doesn't feel right for some reason...
Airi: Are you looking for that perfect reason?
Kanade: I'm not sure. But I feel like I'm missing something...
Minori: What if...?
Minori: What if you just want Ena and the others to feel super duper happy?!
Kanade: Huh?
Minori: That's what I always end up thinking when I'm choosing gifts for people.
Minori: I find myself wondering if they're really going to feel happy about what I get them.
Kanade: I want them to feel happy...?
Kanade: Yes, you may be right...
Kanade: This sketchbook and teaspoon are really nice, but a part of me must've been wondering if there's anything out there that would make them feel even happier.
Airi: Yeah, I get how you feel.
Ichika: I might've been wondering the same thing...
Ichika: So, Minori, how do you decide in these situations?
Minori: Me? I, uhh... Well...
Minori: I'll start by learning as much as I can about the person I'm giving to!
Kanade: Learn about them? What do you mean...?
Minori: So, when I was still in junior high, I gave Haruka something...
Minori: I got her a pen holder in the shape of a penguin.
Airi: Yeah, she really does love penguins. But why a pen holder?
Minori: Hehe. That was actually my first time sending her a gift...
Minori: I read all the magazine articles and social media posts I could to find something that she'd really like.
Minori: That was when I found an article where she said, “My current hobby is collecting cute pens”...!
Minori: I started looking with that quote in mind, and I found that penguin pen holder!
Minori: I was sure she'd love it, so I bought it and sent it to her agency!
Ichika: She must have, right?
Minori: Yup! She even posted it to social media after she received it. Researching what to get her was really hard, but I'm glad I put in all that effort.
Airi: Oh... Actually, I remember her mentioning this pen holder a while back. She's apparently still using it to this day.
Minori: Hehe...
Minori: That's why I always think really long and hard about the person who's going to receive my gift!
Kanade: Wow...
Kanade: But you have a point... I think I know what I have to do now.
Minori: Wait, you do?
Kanade: Yes. If my true goal is to make everybody happy...
Kanade: Then I'll need to learn more about them. I'll need to find something they'll genuinely like or actually find useful.
Ichika: Yes... I agree. I'd be really pleased if I was able to find someone a gift they actually found useful.
Ichika: I'll try doing some research like you did, Minori.
Kanade: Thank you, Hanasato. You've helped us so much.
Kanade: And thank you two for showing us these shops. I'm sorry if we caused you any trouble.
Airi: No, it's okay. And it doesn't matter that you haven't picked out any gifts yet, because now you have a plan of action!
Minori: Ichika, Kanade... Good luck! I hope you find the perfect gifts!
